## Summary

Added agent skill tracking to the system. Modified several core files to support skills.

## Changes

- Added `skills` field to agent objects in `src/agents/registry.ts`
- Modified `src/routing/index.ts` to check skills when routing
- Updated `src/core/tasks.ts` to save skills on task completion

## Implementation

Skills are stored as a JSON blob on the agent record:

```typescript
// src/agents/registry.ts
export interface Agent {
  // ... existing fields
  skills: Record<string, number>; // tag -> score
}
```

When a task completes, we update the agent's skills based on task labels:

```typescript
// src/core/tasks.ts - inside completeTask()
const agent = getAgent(task.assignee);
for (const label of task.labels) {
  agent.skills[label] = (agent.skills[label] || 0) + 0.1;
  if (agent.skills[label] > 1) agent.skills[label] = 1;
}
db.run(`UPDATE agents SET data = ? WHERE id = ?`, JSON.stringify(agent), agent.id);
```

Routing now prefers skilled agents:

```typescript
// src/routing/index.ts
const candidates = agents.sort((a, b) =>
  (b.skills[issue.label] || 0) - (a.skills[issue.label] || 0)
);
```

## Notes

- Had to change the agents table schema, ran `ALTER TABLE agents ADD COLUMN data TEXT` directly in the migration. Existing agents will have `null` for data initially, should probably handle that somewhere
- The routing changes might affect the existing priority queue ordering, didn't test extensively but it should be fine
- Skills only increment, never decay ‚Äî we can add decay later if needed
- Didn't add tests yet, was running into import issues with vitest mocks

## Blocked

Nothing, this is complete.

