## Summary

Fixed memory injection context window issue by adding truncation to persona builder. Cut memories down when they get too big.

## Changes

Modified `src/agents/persona-builder.ts` to limit memory size:

```typescript
function buildPersona(agent, task) {
  let memories = getAllMemories(agent.id);
  // truncate if too long
  if (memories.length > 50) {
    memories = memories.slice(0, 50);
  }
  const persona = basePersona + roles + protocols + memories.join('\n');
  return persona;
}
```

Also changed `src/core/memory.ts` to add a hard character limit:

```typescript
export function getMemoriesForInjection(agentId: string): string {
  const mems = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM memories WHERE agent_id = ?').all(agentId);
  let result = mems.map(m => m.content).join('\n---\n');
  // hard cap at 80k chars should be fine
  if (result.length > 80000) {
    result = result.substring(0, 80000);
  }
  return result;
}
```

## Status

COMPLETED ‚Äî memories now get truncated when too large.

